The paper deals with the algorithmic study of two-player concurrent mean-payoff games, which are a topic of interest in game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The focus is on ergodic games, which involve the concept of stationary strategies and the study of their complexity (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and their complexity (cs.AI), as well as the use of value-iteration algorithms and their efficiency (cs.LG).
